# Unit test for the calculation of the doppler-shifted cross section.
# The performance of the numerical algorithm vs. the analytical approximation is tested for different ratios of Gamma and Delta. 
# For Gamma/Delta << 1, the analytical expression is a good approximation, and the numerical algorithm should give the same result.
# The output file names contain the effective temperature that was used in the calculation, and the ratio Gamma/Delta.
# Minimum and maximum energy for the calculation in eV
4.999990e6, 5.000010e6
# Primary beam intensity distribution
const, 1.0
# 0) Identifier of the target (string)
CrossSection_Test_10K_0.74_Analytic
# 1) Resonance energies in eV (comma separated values)
5.e6
# 2) Transition widths to the ground state in eV (comma separated values)
0.5
# 3) Total transition widths in eV (comma separated values)
0.5
# 4) Angular momentum of the ground state
0
# 5) Angular momenta of the excited states (comma separated values)
1
# 6) Model for velocity distribution
maxwell_boltzmann_approximation, 10.
# 7) Nuclear mass in atomic mass units
100.
# 8) Mass attenuation coefficient
Ce
# 9) Target thickness in atoms/fm^2
0.0001
